    "In other words, the small sample corrections may not be trustworthy and overly conservative in multiple-comparison tests (Joshi et al., 2022).",
    "In their attempt to overcome these problems, Joshi et al.",
    "The Quantitative Methods for Psychology 6 2 (2022) developed an alternative method for correcting RVE when the number of studies is limited.",
    "Their technique is based on cluster wild bootstrapping (CWB), which involves re-sampling of entire clusters from the original effect size data (Cameron et al., 2008).",
    "This technique does not require a large number of clusters nor that clusters have the same size."
  ],
